 Earn A Tech-Infused Degree Online


















 























 

    EARN A RECOGNIZED DEGREE ONLINE FROM AN ACCREDITED UNIVERSITY




Whether you’re taking your first college courses, studying at the undergraduate or graduate level, or transferring to finish your degree, as an online education student at DeVry University, you can prepare to tackle the challenges of the modern workplace and make an impact in your field.

DeVry University is accredited by the Higher Learning Commission (HLC), www.hlcommission.org, signaling that DeVry meets key standards used to evaluate colleges for their focus on quality, student support, transferability of credits and more. Our online degree programs offer you that same credibility, with tech-forward curriculum, dedicated faculty, and personalized support from day one, through graduation day and beyond.




    IMMERSIVE, ENGAGING ONLINE LEARNING 




As you pursue your online degree, you won’t have to worry about sacrificing the benefits of tech-infused, immersive learning we offer here at DeVry. As an online student, you’ll still be able to interact with the university professors who will be teaching your classes, take part in an active community of students and alumni, and participate in extracurricular activities like career-relevant club events, competitions, guest speaker presentations and more. We’re pleased to offer you the same quality of education students receive on campus, along with the convenience of connecting from your tablet, mobile phone or computer.




    THE FLEXIBILITY OF ONLINE LEARNING




Study from home, the office, a café—anywhere you can find a connection. Our online degree programs let you work towards earning a degree while living your life.


Our online options are designed for flexibility, so you can plan your study time to fit your schedule.
Year-round class offerings can help you earn your degree on your own timeline.


With 55+ locations across the United States, our online students also have the option to study on campus.





    Note:
  
Program availability varies by location.




